13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-7-111 of Title 27A, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Spring
18 Creek Watershed Study Act”.
19 B. The Legislature finds that:
20 1. Increasing pressure from agriculture and residential
21 development as well as stream bank erosion and other activities have
22 led to declining water quality levels in the Northeast Oklahoma
23 watershed known as Spring Creek located in Cherokee, Delaware, and
24 Mayes counties near Kansas, Oklahoma, resulting in increased concern
