5 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-7-112 of Title 27A, unless
7 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 A. 1. The Oklahoma Conservation Commission shall undertake a
9 comprehensive watershed-based water quality plan designed to improve
10 and protect the water quality and aquatic habitat in the Spring
11 Creek watershed through the utilization of voluntary, incentive-
12 based programs.
13 2. On or before June 1, 2026, the Commission shall publish an
14 electronic report of the findings. The Commission may, from time to
15 time, update such findings as conditions change and pertinent
16 information becomes available.
17 B. The Commission may contract and cooperate with the Natural
18 Resources Conservation Service of the United States Department of
19 Agriculture and the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency to conduct
20 activities provided for in this section.
21 C. The Commission may apply for and accept grants, gifts, or
22 other sources of public and private funds to carry out the purposes
23 of the Spring Creek Watershed Study Act.
