1 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-7-113 of Title 27A, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
5 for the Oklahoma Conservation Commission to be designated the
6 “Spring Creek Watershed Study Cash Fund Revolving Fund”. The fund
7 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
8 and shall consist of all monies received by the Commission from
9 appropriations by the Legislature to the fund, and any money
10 received as gifts, grants, or other contributions from public or
11 private sources provided for the purpose of implementing the Spring
12 Creek Watershed Study Act. All monies accruing to the credit of the
13 fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
14 Commission for the purpose provided for in this act. Expenditures
15 from the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State
16 Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with the
17 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
18 approval and payment.
19 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
